brahmayaJNa|ब्रह्मयज्ञ
brahma-yajña  (EI 22;<BR>CII 4), study of the Vedas;<BR>name of a mahāyajña.

braahmii|ब्राह्मी
Brāhmī,  name of an early Indian alphabet, from which a large number of alphabets of India and some other countries have derived.

brahmottara|ब्रह्मोत्तर
brahmottara  (IE 8-5), Bengali;<BR>corrupt form of brahmatrā. (IA 15), explained as ‘the sanctuary of a temple’.

bRha|बृह
Bṛha,  abbreviation of Bṛhatpuruṣa (q. v.). See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 143.

bRhachChulka|बृहच्छुल्क
