kappa|कप्प
kappa  (EI 33), Kannaḍa;<BR>same as Sanskrit śulka or kara. (SITI), Tamil-Telugu-Kannaḍa;<BR>periodical and customary payments by persons engaged in some professions.

kara|कर
kara  (IE 8-5), explained by a commentator as ‘the dues  (bhāga) to be realised by the king for the enjoyment of royal land by using it for cultivation and for grazing cattle’;<BR>tax in general. (IE 8-5) rent or tax to be paid in grains when mentioned side by side with hiraṇya. (HRS), tax in general, according to the lexicons;<BR>according to the Arthaśāstra, (1) periodical tax over and above the king's customary grain-share;<BR>(2) emergecy tax levied upon the villagers over and above the normal grain-share;<BR>(3) tax upon merchants' profits. (EI 29;<BR>Chamba;<BR>CITD), a tax or impost;<BR>royal revenue;<BR>rent, dues;<BR>toll, tribute. (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.

karaghaTikaa|करघटिका
karaghaṭikā  (EI 2), meaning uncertain.

karagraama|करग्राम
kara-grāma  (ASLV;<BR>SITI), a revenue-paying or ryotwari village.

karaiyiidu|करैयीदु
karaiyīdu  (ASLV), system of periodical redistribution of lands.

kaaraka|कारक
kāraka  (IE 7-1-2), ‘six’. Cf. Prakrit Karavaka (EI 12), same as Prakrit Kārāpaka; superintendent of the construction of a building.

karakacha|करकच
