kuuTaayukta|कूटायुक्त
Kūṭāyukta  (EI 22), official designation;<BR>probably Kūṭa (Kūṭaka) and Āyukta.

kuTii|कुटी
kuṭī  (IE 8-8), a factory;<BR>cf. nīla-kuṭī. (LL), a Buddhist temple;<BR>an abbreviation of gandhakuṭī.

kuTila|कुटिल
Kuṭila,  cf. Siddhamātṛkā.

kuTum|कुटुम्
Kuṭum  (EI 33;<BR>LP), abbreviation of Kuṭumbika.

kuTumba|कुटुम्ब
kuṭumba  (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.

kuTumbaxetra|कुटुम्बक्षेत्र
kuṭumba-kṣetra  (CII 4), an ancestral field.

kuTumbavRtti|कुटुम्बवृत्ति
kuṭumba-vṛtti,  cf. Kannaḍa kuttumbitti (EI 18), gift of land for the maintenance of the donee's family.

kuTumbayaatraa|कुटुम्बयात्रा
kuṭumba-yātrā  (EI 12;<BR>BL), name of a religious ceremony;<BR> a procession of the royal family to the temple of the family deity on the occasion of the king's coronation or a marriage in the palace.

kuTumbin|कुटुम्बिन्
Kuṭumbin  (EI 12, 17, 23;<BR>SII 1), a cultivator;<BR>an agriculturist householder;<BR>a householder or ryot.

kuTumbinii|कुटुम्बिनी
kuṭumbinī  (EI 19;<BR>CII 2-1;<BR>ML), originally, ‘the wife of a householder’;<BR>later, ‘wife’ in general (cf. Sel. Ins., p. 164).

kuttumbitti|कुत्तुम्बित्ति
kuttumbitti,  Kannaḍa;<BR>cf. grant of certain towns and kuttumbittis as aṅuga-jīvita or fief (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVI, pp. 81-83);<BR>mentioned along with bhatta-grāma (Sanskrit bhaktagrāma), ‘provision village’ (ibid., Vol. XVIII, p. 193);<BR>probably, Sanskrit kuṭumba-vṛtti, grant made for the maintenance of the donee's family.

kuvara|कुवर
Kuvara  (BL), regional modification of Kumāra. Cf. Kuṁvar (Kuñar), Kunwar, etc. L

labdhi|लब्धि
labdhi,  ‘nine’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 345).

laabha|लाभ
lābha  (IE 7-1-2), ‘eleven’.

