lochana|लोचन
locana  (IE 7-1-2), ‘two’.

loha|लोह
loha,  cf. so-loha-lavaṇ-ākara (IE 8-5), ‘together with mines of metals and salt pits [the right of which normally belonged to the king]’.

lohacharmakaara|लोहचर्मकार
