rath-otsava  (EI 16), car-festival.

rathyaa|रथ्या
rathyā  (EI 19), a street.

rati|रति
rati, ratī  (IE 8-8;<BR>IA 19), also spelt rattī; a small weight;<BR>see Sanskrit raktikā.

raaTi|राटि
rāṭi  (LP), ‘a cry’;<BR>cf. Gujarātī rād8.

ratna|रत्न
ratna  (IE 7-1-2), ‘five’;<BR>sometimes also used to indicate ‘nine’, and rarely even ‘fourteen’. (EI 22;<BR>CII 4), same as the Buddhist tri-ratna, i. e. the Buddha, Dharma and Saṅgha. (ML), a relic [of the Buddha]. 

ratnadhenu|रत्नधेनु
ratna-dhenu  (EI 13, 16, 24), name of a mahādāna.

ratnagRha|रत्नगृह
ratna-gṛha  (CII 3), ‘the jewel-house’;<BR>the house enshrining the three ratṅas, regarded by some as denoting a great Buddhist stūpa. (EI 19;<BR>LL), Buddhist;<BR>a sanctuary;<BR>the sanctuary of a Buddha image.

ratnaashva|रत्नाश्व
ratn-āśva  (EI 24), name of a mahādāna.

ratnatraya|रत्नत्रय
ratna-traya  (EI 8), Jain;<BR>samyag-darśana, samyag-jñāna and samyak-cāritra. (EI 27, 30, 31), Buddhist;<BR>the tri-ratna or trinity;<BR>a Buddhist religious establishment enshrining the three ratnas; rent-free land in its possession (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXX, p. 46). Cf. ratnatraya-sambhoga.

ratnatrayasambhoga|रत्नत्रयसम्भोग
ratnatraya-sambhoga  (HRS), traced in Bengal records;<BR>rentfree holding in the possession of Buddhist religious establishments where the Buddha, Dharma and Saṅgha were worshipped;<BR>same as ratna-traya. Cf. rāja-sambhoga.

raTTaguDi|रट्टगुडि
Raṭṭaguḍi  (EI 30), same as Raṭṭoḍī; official designation;<BR>probably the same as Rāṣṭrakūṭa.

raTTagullu|रट्टगुल्लु
Raṭṭagul8l8u  (EI 27), probably, the same as Rāṣṭrakūṭa.

rattii|रत्ती
rattī,  see rati.

raTToDi|रट्टोडि
Raṭṭoḍi  (EI 30), official designation;<BR>same as Raṭṭaguḍi.

raau|राउ
Rāu  (IA 18), same as Rāva (Sanskrit Rājan) or abbreviation of Rāuta (q. v.).

raukyadra|रौक्यद्र
