samanta|समन्त
samanta  (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṁvat.

saamanta|सामन्त
Sāmanta  (IE 8-2;<BR>8-3;<BR>EI 30;<BR>CII 3, 4;<BR>BL;<BR>HD), title of feudatory rulers;<BR>a feudatory smaller than the Rājan; a subordinate chief;<BR>also explained as ‘a minister’ (SITI). See Bomb. Gaz., Vol. XXI, p. 354;<BR>Ep. Ind., Vol. IX, p. 297. Cf. Mahāsāmanta.

saamanta|सामन्त
Sāmanta  (CII 1), a neighbour;<BR>‘one who is in possession of a piece of land in the neighbourhood of the gift land’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 220).

samantabhadra|समन्तभद्र
samantabhadra  (Ep. Ind., Vol. III, p. 199), prosperous on all sides.

saamantaadhikaarin|सामन्ताधिकारिन्
Sāmant-ādhikārin  (ASLV), see Sāmanta and Adhikārin.

saamantaadhipati|सामन्ताधिपति
Sāmant-ādhipati  (EI 16), cf. Mahāsāmant-ādhipati.

saamantapaDiraa|सामन्तपडिरा
Sāmanta-paḍirā  (EI 32), Od8iyā;<BR>Sanskrit Sāmanta-pratirāja; title of a feudatory or nobleman.

saamantika|सामन्तिक
sāmantika,  derived from Sāmanta; chiefship (A.R. Ep., 1958-59, p. 12).

samanthu|समन्थु
samanthu  (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṁvat.

saamaanya|सामान्य
sāmānya,  cf. traividya-sāmānya (EI 23), cāturvedya-sāmānya; ‘belonging to’;<BR>Valabhī-cāturvidya-sāmānya, ‘one of the Caturvedins of Valabhī’;<BR>used also in the sense of vāstavya, ‘resident of…’ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, pp. 172, 176).

samaarachana|समारचन
samāracana,  repairs (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 144).

samaaraNa|समारण
samāraṇa  Prakrit used in Sanskrit for samāracaṇa (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 59).

samaraapaNiiya|समरापणीय
samarāpaṇīya  (LP), to be got repaired;<BR>cf. Gujarātī samrā vavuṁ; see samarcāpanīya, samāracana.

samaraapya|समराप्य
samarāpya  (LP), ‘should be repaired’;<BR>cf. Gujarātī samrāvatruṁ; also samāracana.

samarchaapana|समर्चापन
samarcāpana  (LP), repairing;<BR>cf. samarcāpanīya (LP), ‘to be got repaired’;<BR>cf. samarāpaṇīya; also samāracana.

samasta|समस्त
samasta  (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṁvat especially in medieval Orissan records.

samastamahaasaamantaadhipati|समस्तमहासामन्ताधिपति
Samasta-mahāsāmant-ādhipati  (BL), title of a feudatory ruler of the highest rank. See Mahāsāmant-ādhipati.

samastasenaadhipati|समस्तसेनाधिपति
Samasta-sen-ādhipati  (EI 29, 30), ‘leader of all the forces’;<BR>commander-in-chief. See Sen-ādhipati, Senāpati, Manē2yasamasta-sainy-ādhipati, etc.

samastasuprashastyupeta|समस्तसुप्रशस्त्युपेत
samasta-supraśasty-upeta  (IE 8-2), a royal epithet.

