sāṁśayika  (CII 1), ‘of doubtful value’.

saMskRta|संस्कृत
Saṁskṛta,  see Sanskrit.

saMstava|संस्तव
saṁstava  (CII 1), cf. dharma-saṁstava, ‘acquaintance through Dharma’.

saMsthaa|संस्था
saṁsthā  (HRS), king's dues derived from the marketplace, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.

saMstuta|संस्तुत
saṁstuta  (CII 1), cf. mitra-saṁstuta-jñāti, ‘friends, acquintances and relatives’.

samta|सम्त
samta  (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṁvat. Mta = mat.

samudaaya|समुदाय
Samudāya  (EI 25), official designation.

samudaaya|समुदाय
samudāya  (ASLV), same as gaṇa-bhoga; a tenure in which land is enjoyed by a group of people. (SITI), a village under the gaṇa-bhoga tenure. (SITI), village common;<BR>managing committee of a temple.

samudayabaahya|समुदयबाह्य
samudaya-bāhya  (HRS), occurs in the Damodarpur inscriptions;<BR>‘revenue-free’ or ‘yielding no income’.

samudaayapraapti|समुदायप्राप्ति
samudāya-prāpti, cf. samudāya-ppirātti  (SITI), any acquisition from the village to be enjoyed in common by the villagers.

samudra|समुद्र
Samudra  (EI 10), an epithet of Śiva.

samudra|समुद्र
samudra  (EI 16), same as sapt-āmbhodhi; name of a mahādāna; also means 4 (rarely 7).

samudraghoSha|समुद्रघोष
