samupagata  (EI 12), explained as ‘assembled at’;<BR>really, ‘having connection with’, ‘associated with’;<BR>cf. samupagama, ‘contact’;<BR>also samaveta, upeta, upayāta, etc.

samupaagata|समुपागत
samupāgata  (IE 8-3), ‘associated’;<BR>often explained as ‘assembled’;<BR>but cf. samaveta, samupagata, upayāta, upeta, etc.

samuta|समुत
samuta  (ASLV), same as sammat; an administrative unit. 

samutkriiDaa|समुत्क्रीडा
samutkrīḍā  (EI 15), same as krīḍā or sport.

samva|सम्व
samva  (IE 8-1), mistake for saṁva which is an abbreviation of saṁvatsara.

saMva|संव
saṁva  (IE 8-1) same as saṁvat; contraction of saṁvatsara.

saMvadana|संवदन
saṁvadana  (IE 8-8), submission of information.

saMvartakalpa|संवर्तकल्प
saṁvarta-kalpa  (CII 1), the aeon of destruction.

saMvaasa|संवास
saṁvāsa,  cf. a-kūra-cullaka-vināśi-khaṭvā-saṁvāsa (IE 8-5);<BR>same as āvāsa; shelter or accommodation [which the villagers were obliged to supply to the touring officers of the king].

saMvat|संवत्
saṁvat  (IE 8-1), originally an abbreviation of saṁvatsara (a year) or any of its declensional cases that can be used in expressing a date;<BR>later stereotyped in the sense of ‘a year’ or ‘an era’. It was generally regarded as indeclinable;<BR>but we have some cases of the use of forms with case-endings, e. g., saṁvataḥ, saṁvatā, saṁvati and saṁvatām. See also saṁvate (IE 8-1), the seventh case-ending of saṁvata, a corrupt form of saṁvat. Since the late medieval age, the word specially indicates the Vikrama era, although originally it was used with the name of any reckoning in quoting the dates of records, especially the regnal reckoning. The word is used in inscriptions in a large number of corrupt forms, e. g., samvata, samvatta, samata, samanta, samatta, saṁmat, samasta, smat, samvatu, samvatū, etc., etc.

samvat|सम्वत्
samvat  (IE 8-1), mistake for saṁvat, originally an abbreviation of saṁvatsara.

saMvatsara|संवत्सर
saṁvatsara  (CII 3;BREAḰ;<BR>IA 17), ‘a year’;<BR>‘an cra’, the earlier years of the Indian eras being quoted by this term (or by its abbreviations saṁ, saṁvat, etc.), without any dynastic or other appellation just as in the case of the year of a regnal reckoning.

saaMvatsara|सांवत्सर
Sāṁvatsara  (HD), an astrologer. See Viṣṇu Dh. S., III. 75;<BR>Bṛhatasaṁhitā, 2. 9;<BR>cf. Sāṁvatsarika (EI 5).

saMvatsarapratipadaa|संवत्सरप्रतिपदा
saṁvatsara-pratipadā,  name of a tithi.

saMvatsarashraaddha|संवत्सरश्राद्ध
saṁvatsara-śrāddha  (CII 4), śrāddha performed on the first anniversary of a person's death.

saMvatsaravaariya|संवत्सरवारिय
saṁvatsara-vāriya  (SITI), annual committee appointed by the sabhā; annual committee for supervising the management of village affairs;<BR>also called āṭṭi-vāriyam (SITI) in Tamil.

saMvatsaravimoxashraaddha|संवत्सरविमोक्षश्राद्ध
saṁvatsara-vimokṣa-śrāddha  (CII 4), same as saṁvatsaraśrāddha performed on the first anniversary of a person's death.

saaMvatsarika|सांवत्सरिक
Sāṁvatsarika  (HD), an astrologer. See Paiṭhīnasi quoted  in Hist. Dharm., Vol. III, p. 193.

saaMvatsarikahiraNya|सांवत्सरिकहिरण्य
sāṁvatsarika-hiraṇya  (IE 8-1), annual revenue in cash;<BR>often abbreviated as sāṁ-hi.

samvatta|सम्वत्त
samvatta  (IE 8-1), corrupt form of saṁvat.

