ṣaṭ-catuṣkikā,  cf. cha-cokī.

satera|सतेर
satera, sateraka,  same as Greek stater; regarded as equal to two dīnāras (JNSI, Vol. XV, p. 153).

satii|सती
satī  (EI 6, 30;<BR>CII 3, 4;<BR>BL;<BR>CITD), literally, ‘a chaste woman’;<BR>really ‘a woman burning herself with her husband’. (EI 6, 30), self-immolation of a widow usually on the funeral pyre of her husband;<BR>usually spelt suttee in English.

