śilā-śāsana  (IA 30), a stone-charter;<BR>a document engraved on stone.

shilpin|शिल्पिन्
Śilpin  (EI 4, 8;<BR>BL), epithet of an artist or artisan;<BR>generally, applied to engravers of inscriptions.

shilpakaara|शिल्पकार
Śilpakāra  (EI 32), same as Śilpin.

shilotara|शिलोतर
śilotara  (EI 32), also called śilotarī, śilotra, śilotrī, śilottara; name of a tax or income;<BR>cf. śrotaka.

shilotarii|शिलोतरी
śilotarī  (EI 32), see śilotara, etc.

shilotra|शिलोत्र
śilotra  (EI 32), see śilotara, etc.

shilotrii|शिलोत्री
śilotrī  (EI 32), see śilotara, etc.

shilottara|शिलोत्तर
śilottara  (EI 32), see śilotara, etc.

shilvari|शिल्वरि
śilvari  (EI 23), Tamil;<BR>name of a tax.

siima|सीम
sīma  (IA 18), used for ‘country’ in the areas on the banks of the Kṛṣṇā and the Godāvarī. Cf. Kona-sīma (EI 32), also called a deśa, maṇḍala, sthala, etc.

siimaa|सीमा
sīmā  (EI 11), five types enumerated by Nārada: Dhvajinī matsyinī c = aiva naidhānī bhaya-varjitā | rājaśāsana-nītā ca sīmā pañcavidhā smṛtā (i. e. big trees or hills, rivers or tanks, underground signs and artificial marks made by men and by the king's order). Cf. Tamil śīrmai, śīmai (SITI), a territorial division;<BR>also called sīman.

siimakarmakara|सीमकर्मकर
Sīmakarmakara  (HD), officer in charge of boundaries or of boundary disputes. See CII, Vol. III, pp. 213, 216.

siiman|सीमन्
sīman  (IE 8-4;<BR>ASLV), Kannaḍa sīmē2; a small territorial unit like a Parganā;<BR>the sub-division of a district;<BR>sometimes used to indicate ‘a province’.

siimaavivaada|सीमाविवाद
sīmā-vivāda,  cf. Tamil śīmai-vivādam (SITI), a boundary dispute.

shiimehabbaruva|शीमेहब्बरुव
Śīmē2habbaruva  (ASLV), an officer associated with the administrative unit called sīmai.

siMhanikaa|सिंहनिका
siṁhanikā,  service rendered in lieu of taxes (Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 28). 

siMhapaada|सिंहपाद
siṁha-pāda,  cf. Tamil śiṅga-pādam (SITI), legs of a vessel or vessel-stand in the shape of lion's feet.

siMhaasana|सिंहासन
siṁh-āsana  (EI 29), literally, ‘the lion-seat’;<BR>the throne which was one of the royal insignia. Cf. siṁha-sthāna.

siMhaasanaadhipati|सिंहासनाधिपति
