Śiṣya  (SII 1), a pupil.

siitaa|सीता
sītā  (EI 31), cultivated land. Cf. hala. (HRS), produce of the royal farms, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.

sitachaamara|सितचामर
sita-cāmara  (EI 29), ‘white chowrie’;<BR>one of the royal insignia.

