skandhaavaara|स्कन्धावार
skandhāvāra  (EI 29;<BR>CII 3;<BR>BL), camp;<BR>usually called jaya-skandhāvāra (i. e. the victorious camp) which indicates the capital of a king in some cases. Cf. Kannaḍa neleviḍu = Sanskrit sthira-śibira.

