stuupa|स्तूप
stūpa  (CII 3;<BR>BL;<BR>LL), technical name of a type of Buddhist monument;<BR>a Buddhist structure enshrining relics. Sometimes the term ratna-gṛha (i. e. the house enshrining the three ratnas or the best amongst the three) seems to be used to denote a stūpa. (EI 2), a Jain religious establishment. (SITI), pinnacle of a temple.

