thavaNii|थवणी
thavaṇī  (HA), a wooden stand used as a symbol for the teacher or the Tīrthaṅkara, a religious text or certain prescribed small objects being placed on it and worshipped by Jain monks;<BR>same as sthāpan-ācārya.

Theka|ठेक
