urvaraa|उर्वरा
urvarā  (IE 7-1-2), ‘one’.

uShara|उषर
uṣara,  cf. sa-gartt-oṣara (IE 8-5);<BR>a saline spot or barren land.

ushaavaDi|उशावडि
uśāvaḍi  (IE 8-4;<BR>SITI), a subdivision of the district;<BR>same as śāvaḍi or cāvaḍi.

UShmala|ऊष्मल
ūṣmala  (EI 12), glowing.

uShNiSha|उष्णिष
uṣṇiṣa,  cf. Prakrit uṁnisa (EI 20;<BR>LL), a coping stone. (EI 8), protuberance of the Buddha's skull.

utkalita|उत्कलित
utkalita,  cf. kaṭakam=utkalitam (IA 14, 30), ‘the camp was pitched’.

utkara|उत्कर
utkara  (IE 8-5), probably, minor taxes;<BR>but see kāru-kara. Cf. upakara, nikara, etc. But see also Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 47.

utkarNita|उत्कर्णित
utkarṇita  (LP), frightened.

utkarSha|उत्कर्ष
utkarṣa  (CII 1), used in the sense of utkṛṣṭa.

utkhaatakaarmaNa|उत्खातकार्मण
Utkhātakārmaṇa  (EI 15), epithet of a donee.

utkheTana|उत्खेटन
utkheṭana  (EI 32;<BR>HRS), known from certain records from Assam;<BR>explained as an impost levied upon the villagers on specified occasions;<BR>probably, the trouble of free labour. Cf. Utkheṭayitā, Autkheṭika.

utkheTayitaa|उत्खेटयिता
Utkheṭayitā  (EI 12;<BR>BL;<BR>HRS), known from certain Assam records;<BR>explained as a tax-collector;<BR>officer in charge of utkheṭana (q. v.);<BR>same as Autkheṭika.

utkiirNa|उत्कीर्ण
utkīrṇa  (CII 3), ‘engraved’;<BR>a technical expression for the actual engravign of an inscription on copper or stone;<BR>sometimes indicated by the word udghāṭita (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXI, p. 20) and ghaṭita (Ind. Ant., Vol. XII, p. 121). See Ullekhaka, likhita. 

utkoTa|उत्कोट
utkoṭa  (IE 8-5, 8-8;<BR>EI 33), Prakrit ukkoḍa; a levy;<BR>customary presents to be made on occasions to the king or landlord and others. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 56.

utkRR|उत्कॄ
ut-kṝ,  ‘to engrave’;<BR>cf. Prakrit kaṇḍāra, used in some Kannaḍa inscriptions (Bul. Dec. Col. Res. Inst., Vol. XI, 1950, pp. 170-71). Cf. utkīrṇa, udghāṭita, Ullekhaka, Vilekhaka.

utkRShTi|उत्कृष्टि
utkṛṣṭi  (IE 8-8;<BR>EI 30), same as Prakrit ukkuṭṭhī (q. v.), Sanskrit utkrośa; wailing.

utkrosha|उत्क्रोश
utkrośa  (IE 8-8), see utkṛṣṭi.

utkRti|उत्कृति
utkṛti  (IE 7-1-2), ‘twentysix’;<BR>rarely ‘twentyone’.

utpadyamaanaviShTika|उत्पद्यमानविष्टिक
utpadyamāna-viṣṭika  (CII 4), ‘with the right to unpaid labour as occasion may arise’;<BR>a privilege attached to gift lands.

utpanna|उत्पन्न
utpanna,  decided or acertained (Select Inscriptions, pp. 284, 286);<BR>same as pratipanna; cf. pratipad.

utpaaT|उत्पाट्
ut-pāṭ  (LP), Gujarātī upāḍavuṁ; cf. Vaidyanātha-patram= utpāṭayati, ‘takes a bilva-patra of the god Vaidyanātha (Śiva)’, i. e. swears.

utpaata|उत्पात
utpāta  (EI 33), unusual phenomenon.

utpaTTa|उत्पट्ट
utpaṭṭa,  cf. upaṭṭa (EI 13), abundance;<BR>exuberance or overflowing [expecially of rich dishes at a feast].

utpatti|उत्पत्ति
utpatti  (EI 12), cf. samast-otpatti-sahita, ‘together with all the produce (or income)’.

utsaaha|उत्साह
utsāha  (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 189), generous gift, bounty.

utsaahashakti|उत्साहशक्ति
utsāha-śakti  (CII 4), personal energy.

utsanga|उत्सङ्ग
utsaṅga  (HRS), extra cess levied upon villagers and citizens on occasions of festival events, such as the birth of a prince, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.

utsarpaNa|उत्सर्पण
utsarpaṇa,  cf. pañca-mahāyajña-kriy-otsarpaṇ-ārtham (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXV, p. 279, text lines 64-65).

utsarpita|उत्सर्पित
utsarpita  (CII 1), erected.

utsRta|उत्सृत
utsṛta  (CII 1) = ucchrita, man of a high position;<BR>a rich man.

utta|उत्त
utta  (LP), modification of Sanskrit putra.

uttamadaani|उत्तमदानि
uttama-dāni  (SITI), a gift made without expecting any merit for the same;<BR>a superior kind of gift.

uttamagosaasa|उत्तमगोसास
uttama-gosāsa  (IA 11), meaning uncertain.

uttamottama|उत्तमोत्तम
uttam-ottama  (EI 25), a type of temple.

uttaanadvaadashi|उत्तानद्वादशि
uttāna-dvādaśi  (SITI), twelfth day of the bright fortnight in the month of Kārttigai when the god Viṣṇu is believed to wake up from his sleep;<BR>see utthāna-dvādaśī. 

uttara|उत्तर
uttara,  cf. uttarāṇi (LP), same as uttar-ākṣarāṇi. See akṣara.

uttaara|उत्तार
uttāra  (SITI), a regular fixed payment;<BR>same as uddhāra.

uttarakulika|उत्तरकुलिक
Uttarakulika  (EI 30), a class of officials.

uttarakulikavaarika|उत्तरकुलिकवारिक
Uttarakulika-vārika  (IE 8-8), an official designation of uncertain import. See Vārika.

uttaramantrin|उत्तरमन्त्रिन्
Uttara-mantrin  (EI 8;<BR>SITI), the chief minister.

uttaraniyoga|उत्तरनियोग
uttara-niyoga  (EI 32), ‘subsequent assignment’;<BR>cf. uktaniyoga.

uttarasabhaa|उत्तरसभा
uttara-sabhā  (EI 19), the supreme assembly.

uttaravaada|उत्तरवाद
uttara-vāda  (SITI), a guarantee;<BR>responsibility.

uttaraayaNa|उत्तरायण
uttar-āyaṇa  (IA 17;<BR>SII 1), the winter solstice;<BR>the period during which the sun gradually moves from south to north;<BR>cf. dakṣiṇ-āyana.

utthaana|उत्थान
utthāna  (CII 1), exerting oneself.

utthaanadvaadashii|उत्थानद्वादशी
utthāna-dvādaśī  (Ep. Ind., Vol. XVIII, pp. 163, 167, 169), name of a tithi (EI 9);<BR>twelfth day of the bright fortnight in the month of Kārttigai when the god Viṣṇu is believed to wake up from his sleep (SITI).

utthaaya|उत्थाय
utthāya,  ‘of one's own accord’ (Select Inscriptions, p. 248).

utthitaasanin|उत्थितासनिन्
Utthit-āsanin  (IE 8-3);<BR>see Autthilāsanika.

uttiram|उत्तिरम्
uttiram  (SII 2), the projecting part of a wall.

uvaTaka|उवटक
uvaṭaka  (EI 1), probably, a verandah, porch or vestibule;<BR>cf. Marāṭhī oṭī. V

va|व
va  (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vaḍḍavāra (Saturday or Thursday).

va|व
va  (CII 3;<BR>IA 8-1), an abbreviation of vadya or ‘the dark fortnight’ or else a substitute for ba (abbreviation of bahula) used in connection with di; see ba-di, va-di.

va|व
va, vā  (IE 8-1), abbreviation of Prakrit vassa or vāsa- Sanskrit varṣā, the rainy season.

vaa|वा
vā  (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vāra. Cf. vā-bhū, vā-ṭī. (LP), abbreviation of Vāṇija, a merchant.

vaabhuu|वाभू
vā-bhū  (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vāstu-bhūmi, ‘homestead land.’

vaachaka|वाचक
Vācaka  (LL), a Jain preacher.

vachana|वचन
vacana  (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’. 

vachanakaara|वचनकार
Vacanakāra  (EI 23), an author of vacanas or sayings;<BR>cf. subhāṣita.

vaachanika|वाचनिक
vācanika,  cf. rāja-vāchanika (CII 1), a royal order.

vachogupti|वचोगुप्ति
vaco-gupti  (CII 1), restraint in the matter of speech.

vaaDa|वाड
vāḍa  (CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa;<BR>a street, a range of houses. (EI 11), a ward. (IA 7), also vāḍi; often suffixed to geographical names. (CII 4), name of a tax.

vaaDa|वाड
vāḍa, vāḍā  (IE 8-4), corrupt forms of pāṭaka, ‘part of a village’;<BR>in soem dialects, also ‘a village’;<BR>often suffixed to the names of localities.

vaDaharaka|वडहरक
Vaḍaharaka  (EI 11), same as Marvād8ī (Marwari) Baḍero; an old man.

vaDDaachaarya|वड्डाचार्य
Vaḍḍ-ācārya  (SII 11-1), Sanskrit Vṛddh-ācārya or Bṛhad-ācārya; designation of a Jain teacher.

vaDDavaara|वड्डवार
vaḍḍa-vāra  (EI 13;<BR>CITD), Telugu-Kannaḍa;' Saturday or Thursday (A. Venkatasubbiah, Some Śaka Dates in Inscriptions, pp. 57. ff.);<BR>same as bṛha-vāra. The word in the Telugu part of an inscription is explained as śanaiścara-vāra in the Sanskrit portion of the said record;<BR>sometimes wrongly supposed to stand for some other day, e. g. Friday (IA 23) or Sunday (Venkatasubbiah, op. cit., p. 58). Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 147;<BR>XIII, p. 16;<BR>Vol. XXXI, p. 100, note 1;<BR>Vol. XXXIII, p. 1, note 2;<BR>Ind. Ant., Vol. XXII, pp. 111, 251-52;<BR>XXIII, p. 168. Vaḍḍa=vṛddha or bṛhat.

vaDDavyavahaari|वड्डव्यवहारि
Vaḍḍa-vyavahāri  (SITI;<BR>ASLV), the leader of a merchant guild;<BR>a banker;<BR>the principal money-changer;<BR>chief of the Nānādeśi (non-local) merchants. Cf. Mahāvaḍḍavyavahāri.

vaDavaa|वडवा
Vaḍavā  (EI 22, 27), Marāṭhil;<BR>record-keeper.

vaadha|वाध
vādha  (EI 16), land measure.

vaadhaa|वाधा
vādhā,  cf. bādhā.

vaaDhaDhaa|वाढढा
vāḍhaḍhā  (IA 15), a doubtful word probably meaning ‘a drum’.

vadhrikukkuTa|वध्रिकुक्कुट
vadhri-kukkuṭa  (IA 18, CII 1), Prakrit vadhi-kukuṭa; a capon;<BR>also Sanskritised as vṛddhi-kukkuṭa.

vadhuu|वधू
vadhū,  one's own wife;<BR>one's son's wife. (putra-vadhū)

vadi|वदि
va-di  (IE 8-1), abbreviation of vadya-pakṣa-dina or a mistake for ba-di (q. v.).

vaaDi|वाडि
vāḍi  (IA 7), same as vāḍa; often suffixed to geographical names. 

vaadya|वाद्य
vādya  (SITI), a musical instrument.

vaadyamahaaraaja|वाद्यमहाराज
