vagaira|वगैर
vagaira  (IA 20), Persian;<BR>‘and so forth’.

vaagulii|वागुली
Vāgulī  (EI 28), Od8iyā;<BR>also written Bāgulī; the king's betel-bearer;<BR>same as Vārgulika, etc.

vaagulika|वागुलिक
Vāgulika, Vāgūlika  (CII 4;<BR>BL), explained by some as ‘a seller of betel-leaves’;<BR>the bearer of the betel-box of an Orissan ruler;<BR>same as Vārgulika, etc.

vaaguNi|वागुणि
Vāguṇi  (EI 24), mistake for Vāguli.

vaha|वह
vaha,  cf. a-vaha (IE 8-5);<BR>[free]<BR>carrying of loads [which the villagers had to provide for the touring officers of the king or land-lord];<BR>may also be a horse for the use of the officers. (EI 31;<BR>IA 18;<BR>CII 4), a streamlet;<BR>a water-channel. (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIV, p. 177), a common highway.

vaaha|वाह
vāha,  cf. Vāha-nāyaka.

vaahaka|वाहक
Vāhaka  (EI 3), probably, a driver or attendant of cattle.

vaahalaa|वाहला
vāhalā  (EI 3), a water course.

vaahali|वाहलि
Vāhali  (BL), official designation explained as ‘the lord of horses’.

vahamaana|वहमान
vahamāna  (LP), cf. vahamāna-hala-balīvarda, ‘bullocks used in ploughing land’;<BR>vahamāna-samakara-bhūmi in which vahamāna means ‘[the land that is]<BR>being ploughed’. (LP), travelling.

vaahana|वाहन
vāhana  (LP), a load-carrier;<BR>a cart, ship, etc. See vahitra.

vaahanaayaka|वाहनायक
Vāha-nāyaka  (EI 23), official designation;<BR>probably, ‘the officer in charge of the king's Khās Mahāls’ (from vāha, a plough);<BR>may also be the superintendent of transport. See vāhoṭaka.

vahikaa|वहिका
vahikā  (LP), an account book.

vaahiniipati|वाहिनीपति
Vāhinīpati  (EI 28;<BR>IA 10), leader of forces;<BR>a general;<BR>cf. Senāpati, etc.

vahaNi|वहणि
vahaṇi  (IA 18), meaning uncertain.

vahitra|वहित्र
vahitra  (IE 8-5, 8-8;<BR>EI 30), boat or any large carrier like a cart;<BR>see vāhana. Cf. sārtha-vahitreṣu praveśe nirgame ca pratyekaṁ rūpakaḥ devasya yātr-otsave dātavyaḥ (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 232). (IE 8-8), cf. bhāṇḍa-bhṛta-vahitra, ‘a wagon full of pots or jars’. 

vahni|वह्नि
vahni  (IE 7-1-2), ‘three’.

vaahoTaka|वाहोटक
vāhoṭaka  (LP), either Gujarātī vighoṭi, an assessment of land collected per vighā (bīghā), or the plough tax (i. e. land tax) from vāha, a plough.

vaahyaali|वाह्यालि
vāhyāli  (BL), explained as ‘stables’;<BR>cf. bāhy-āli. (EI 6), explained as ‘a camp’.

vahni|वह्नि
vahni  (EI 33), ‘three’.

vaibhoga|वैभोग
