vana-durga  (ASLV), fort built in the midst of forests.

vaNajaaraka|वणजारक
Vaṇajāraka,  also spelt Vaṇijāraka (EI 11), same as the Vanjārī of Rājasthān, whose hereditary calling is to carry grains on pack-bullocks;<BR>cf. Vaṇijjāraka.

vandaapanaa|वन्दापना
vandāpanā  (IE 8-5;<BR>EI 12, 33), Od8iyā;<BR>presents to be made on meeting the king or landlord;<BR>same as Persian nazrāna; cf. vijaya-vandāpanā.

vangaalii|वङ्गाली
Vaṅgālī,  see Bengali which is its Anglicised spelling.

vaaNija|वाणिज
