Viśvakarman  (LL), an architect.

vishvaala|विश्वाल
Viśvāla  (EI 31), Od8iyā;<BR>a village watchman.

vishvaasa|विश्वास
Viśvāsa  (EI 24), official designation;<BR>same as Vaiśvāsika; cf. the titles Viśvāsa-Khāna, Viśvāsa-rāya, etc., conferred by the Muslim rulers especially in the Bengal region.

vishvaasana|विश्वासन
viśvāsana  (CII 1), ‘being inspired with faith’.

vishvasattaa|विश्वसत्ता
viśva-sattā  (IA 14), wrong Sanskritisation of Prakrit vasasata (Sanskrit varṣa-śata);<BR>translated as ‘universal rule’. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIV, p. 241, note 1.

vishvaasika|विश्वासिक
Viśvāsika  (EI 24), same as Vaiśvāsika (q. v.), etc.

vishvavishvopaka|विश्वविश्वोपक
Viśvaviśvopaka  (IA 19), Jain;<BR>explained as ‘one whose body and soul exhibit marks of an ācārya’.

vitaana|वितान
vitāna  (SII 13), probably, a canopy.

vitaanaadhipa|वितानाधिप
Vitān-ādhipa  (Ep. Ind., Vol. XIII, p. 325, note 3), supposed to be ‘an officer in charge of the king's bed-chamber’. Cf. Vāsāgārika, Śayyāpāla, etc.

viTapa|विटप
viṭapa  (IE 8-5), a bush;<BR>used in sa-jhāṭa-viṭapa; a branch. Cf. Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 183.

viThavigaara|विठविगार
viṭha-vigāra  (Chamba), unpaid labour;<BR>from Sanskrit viṣṭi and Persian begār.

viithi|वीथि
vīthi, vīthī  (SII 1), a street. (EI 24, 30;<BR>CII 4), a shop;<BR>a stall or shop in a market.  (EI 21, 23, 29, 30), a territorial unit;<BR>the subdivision of a district. (IE 8-4), sometimes a subdivision forming part of a maṇḍala, but sometimes a district forming part of a bhukti or province.

viithiimahattara|वीथीमहत्तर
Vīthī-mahattara  (HD), headman of the territorial unit called vīthī. Cf. IHQ, Vol. XIX, pp. 16, 21.

viithyadhikaraNa|वीथ्यधिकरण
vīthy-adhikaraṇa  (EI 31), administrative office of a subdivision called vīthī.

vittabandha|वित्तबन्ध
vitta-bandha  (CII 4), mortage.

viTTollakara|विट्टोल्लकर
viṭṭolla-kara  (HRS), known from Maitraka records;<BR>explained as the contribution in forced labour.

vivaaha|विवाह
Vivāha  (EI 12), ‘one whose vehicle is the bird’;<BR>i. e. Viṣṇu.

vivaaha|विवाह
vivāha  (CII 1), marriage of a daughter;<BR>cf. āvāha which means the marriage of a son.

vivaahakara|विवाहकर
vivāha-kara,  cf. Tamil kaṇṇāla-kkāṇan (EI 28), the marriage fee;<BR>cf. vivāha-ppaṇam.

vivaahapaNa|विवाहपण
vivāha-paṇa,  cf. vivāha-ppaṇam (SITI), same as kaṇṇālakkāṇam; a tax on marriage.

viviita|विवीत
vivīta  (HRS), royal dues collected by the superintendent of pastures, as suggested by the Arthaśāstra.

viviitaadhyaxa|विवीताध्यक्ष
Vivīt-ādhyakṣa  (EI 28), known from the Arthaśāstra; officer in charge of the pasture land. Cf. Vrajabhūmika.

viyat|वियत्
viyat  (IE 7-1-2), ‘cypher’.

vodaa|वोदा
vodā  (IE 8-5;<BR>EI 29), a kind of levy in Od8iyā records;<BR>same as Od8iyā vadāi, ‘the obligation of offering uncooked food.’

voDii|वोडी
voḍī, voḍrī  (EI 23), (1/4) paṇa; 20 cowrie-shells;<BR>cf. kapardakavoḍī, ‘voḍī counted in cowrie-shells’.

volaapana|वोलापन
volāpana,  see volāpika, vulāvi.

volaapika|वोलापिक
Volāpika  (LP), an officer in charge of collecting the tax called volāpana or vulāvī. It is supposed that a Volāpaka or the men under him accompanied the merchants in their journey for the safety of their goods and the volāpana tax was collected from the merchants for safeguarding their goods.

voTa|वोट
voṭa,  cf. boṭa.

vraja|व्रज
vraja,  see Vraja-bhūmika. Cf. Ghoshal, H. Rev. Syst., p. 110.

vrajabhuumi|व्रजभूमि
vraja-bhūmi  (IE 8-4), grazing land.

vrajabhuumika|व्रजभूमिक
Vrajabhūmika  (CII 1;<BR>EI 2;<BR>HD), Prakrit Vacabhūmika; superintendent of cowpens;<BR>officer in charge of the royal cattle and pasture lands. Cf. Vivīt-ādhyakṣa. 

vrata|व्रत
vrata  (CITD), religious vow;<BR>a self-imposed task;<BR>a religious act of devotion or austerity;<BR>vowed observance;<BR>a vow in general. There are many vratas mentioned in the different Purāṇas. But new vratas crop up in different parts of the country. (EI 4), five in number.

vriihikara|व्रीहिकर
vrīhi-kara,  cf. Tamil arisi-kkāṇam (SITI), a levy for husking paddy into rice.

vRddha|वृद्ध
vṛddha  (LP), participle of vṛdh, ‘to cut’. Cf. Vṛddha-Gaṇeśa (IA 19), ‘the senior Gaṇeśa’.

vRddhadhaanuShka|वृद्धधानुष्क
Vṛddha-dhānuṣka  (IE 8-3), senior archer;<BR>the chief archer.

vRddharaaja|वृद्धराज
Vṛddharāja  (EI 3;<BR>LL), ‘prosperous king’;<BR>title of a pious king.

vRddhi|वृद्धि
vṛddhi  (EI 28), a super tax or the interest on arrears of taxes;<BR>also interest.

vRddhikukkuTa|वृद्धिकुक्कुट
vṛddhi-kukkuṭa  (CII 1), Prakrit vadhi-kukuṭa; a cock that has been caponed;<BR>also Sanskritised as vadhri-kukkuṭa.

vRShataapashaasana|वृषतापशासन
vṛṣatāpa-śāsana  (EI 13), same as tāmra-śāsana.

vRShaviMshopaka|वृषविंशोपक
vṛṣa-viṁśopaka  (Ep. Ind., Vol. XV, p. 39), name of a coin (probably bearing the figure of a bull);<BR>cf. viṁśopaka.

vRtti|वृत्ति
vṛtti  (SITI), means;<BR>livelihood, occupation;<BR>grant of land for one's livelihood. (SII 3), land granted for service. (EI 17, 31;<BR>CITD), share;<BR>share in a village granted to a Brāhmaṇa as a free gift.

vu|वु
Vu d8hā-leṅkā (EI 28), Od8iyā;<BR>official designation;<BR>cf. Leṅkā.

vulaapikaa|वुलापिका
vulāpikā  (LP), tax for the maintenance of the campfollowers;<BR>cf. Gujarātī val8āmaṇ vulāyiyā; also volāpika, vulāviyā (q. v.).

vulaavii|वुलावी
