vyaasa|व्यास
Vyāsa  (EI 11;<BR>PJS), a reciter or exponent;<BR>a Brāhmaṇa  who recites or expounds the epics and Purāṇas in public. Cf. Paurāṇika.

vyasana|व्यसन
vyasana  (CII 1), misfortune.

vyaaShedha|व्याषेध
vyāṣedha  (LP), vyāṣedhaḥ kāritaḥ or niṣedhaḥ kāritaḥ, ‘proved the countrary [in the court that it was his own land and not ḍohalikā land’];<BR>vahamāna-bhūmi-vyāṣedha, ‘no one should stop him when he is ploughing his own piece of land’. (LP), seizure;<BR>confiscation as government property.

vyatikara|व्यतिकर
vyatikara  (LP), ‘in connection with’.

vyatiipaata|व्यतीपात
vyatīpāta  (IA 19), used in relation to eclipses.

vyava|व्यव
Vyava  (LP), abbreviation of Vyavahārika in the sense of a dealer, a money-lender, a merchant.

vyavachChinna|व्यवच्छिन्न
vyavacchinna,  fixed (Select Inscriptions, p. 237);<BR>demarcated.

vyavahaara|व्यवहार
vyavahāra,  cf. vyavahāra-pade (LP), ‘as a tax from merchants’.

vyavahaaraabhilekhitaka|व्यवहाराभिलेखितक
